#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:145
msgid ""
"Other things that could be taken into account, besides the sub-measures "
"below:"
msgstr ""
"Otras cuestiones que se pueden tener en cuenta, además de las submedidas que "
"se desarrollan más adelante:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:147
msgid "How easy the different components are to adapt and develop"
msgstr "Facilidad de adaptación y evolución de los diferentes componentes"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:149
msgid "Immediate and long-term costs, including starting costs"
msgstr ""
"Coste inmediato y coste a largo plazo, incluyendo los costes de salida"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:151
msgid "Existence of a local or global support network or informal community"
msgstr "Existencia de una comunidad informal o red de soporte local y global"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:153
msgid "Innovative solutions (and the value that brings)"
msgstr "Soluciones innovadoras (y valor que eso aporta)"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:155
msgid "Impact on data privacy and sovereignty"
msgstr "Impacto sobre la privacidad y la soberanía de datos"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:160
#, no-wrap
msgid "Choose components with a licence approved by the FSF or the OSI"
msgstr ""
"Escoger componentes con una licencia aprobada por la OSI o por la FSF "

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:170
msgid "The two sets of valid licences are almost identical:"
msgstr "Los dos conjuntos de licencias válidas son casi idénticos:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:172
msgid "https://www.gnu.org/licenses/license-list.en.html"
msgstr "https://www.gnu.org/licenses/license-list.es.html"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:173
msgid "https://opensource.org/licenses"
msgstr "https://opensource.org/licenses"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select components with a greater diversity and weight of contributors"
msgstr ""
"Favorecer componentes con una mayor diversidad y peso de los contribuyentes "

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:189
msgid ""
"Here we understand contributions in a broad sense: commits in the code "
"repository, bug reports, translations, etc."
msgstr ""
"Aquí entendemos contribuciones en un sentido amplio: commits en el "
"repositorio de código, bug reports, traducciones, etcétera."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:191
msgid ""
"Diversity (different people and organisations involved) is more important "
"than the number of contributions (e.g. the number of commits per month)."
msgstr ""
"Es más importante la diversidad (personas y entidades diferentes que "
"participan) que la cantidad de las contribuciones (por ejemplo, número de "
"commits por mes)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:194
msgid ""
"If the component shows contributions by important organisations (companies "
"of a certain size, universities, institutions), it is very likely that, even "
"if some contributions fail, the project will continue.  But it could also be "
"a very good sign that lots of people make contributions on an individual "
"basis and these are taken into account."
msgstr ""
"Si el componente presenta contribuciones por parte de organizaciones "
"importantes (empresas de un cierto tamaño, universidades, instituciones), es "
"más probable que, aunque alguno de los contribuyentes falle, el proyecto "
"continúe. Pero también puede ser muy buena señal que muchas personas a "
"título individual hagan contribuciones y que se tengan en cuenta."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select components with recent activity"
msgstr "Favorecer componentes con actividad reciente "

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:205
msgid "First of all we need to look at the bug tracker, noting:"
msgstr ""
"En primer lugar, hay que analizar la actividad en el bug tracker y observar "
"lo siguiente:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:208
msgid ""
"The number of defects notified.  We shouldn’t panic if there are a lot of "
"open and unsolved notifications, because the number of issues and bugs tends "
"to grow in a straight line with the number of users but the number of "
"developers usually grows more slowly."
msgstr ""
"La cantidad de notificaciones de deficiencias. No nos tiene que alarmar que "
"haya muchas notificaciones abiertas y no resueltas, el número de incidencias "
"tiende a crecer linealmente con el número de usuarios, pero, en cambio, el "
"número de desarrolladores suele crecer más lentamente."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:212
msgid ""
"Let the developers gradually respond to the issues.  We want to stress this "
"point: if there are a large number of users, there will always be lots of "
"open issues.  The important thing is to see whether the developers are "
"regularly involved in the bug tracker, that they haven't abandoned it."
msgstr ""
"Que los desarrolladores estén respondiendo a las incidencias. Insistimos: si "
"el número de usuarios es elevado, habrá siempre muchas incidencias abiertas, "
"pero es importante observar que los desarrolladores participan habitualmente "
"en el bug tracker, que no lo hayan abandonado."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:214
msgid ""
"Then it is important to look at the project's public activity, bearing in "
"mind:"
msgstr ""
"Después hay que mirar la actividad pública del proyecto, teniendo en cuenta "
"lo siguiente:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:216
msgid ""
"How long ago the latest releases were published, news items were posted in a "
"blog or similar site."
msgstr ""
"Antigüedad de las últimas releases públicas, noticias publicadas en forma de "
"blog o similar."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:217
msgid ""
"The tone, usefulness and diversity of the participants in the project's "
"discussion forums and public communication channels."
msgstr ""
"El tono, la utilidad y la diversidad de participantes en el foros de "
"discusión y canales de comunicación públicos del proyecto."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select components with full and up-to-date documentation"
msgstr "Favorecer componentes con una documentación completa y al día "

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:228
msgid ""
"When the documentation is in a public repository and there is a good range "
"of people contributing to it, that too is a very good sign."
msgstr ""
"Que la documentación esté en un repositorio público y que haya bastante "
"diversidad de personas que contribuyan también es una muy buena señal."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:232
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select components where there is commercial support available"
msgstr "Favorecer componentes para los que exista soporte comercial "

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:245
msgid ""
"When products have a free software licence, it will always be possible to "
"contact someone to get them modified, maintained or have problems solved.  "
"However, we have more guarantee of success if there are already companies or "
"people offering professional support for the component in question, and it "
"can therefore be assumed they are very familiar with it."
msgstr ""
"En productos con licencia libre, siempre será posible contratar a alguien a "
"fin de que los modifique y mantenga o resuelva problemas. No obstante, "
"obtenemos una mayor garantía de éxito si ya existen empresas o personas que "
"ofrecen soporte profesional sobre el componente en cuestión, y que, por lo "
"tanto, se puede asumir que lo conocen bien."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:249
msgid ""
"It is better if there are various companies offering commercial services in "
"relation to the product than just one, because in the latter case we would "
"be more dependent on that company.  It is a normal business model for the "
"company that develops the product (perhaps without hardly any external "
"community support) to also offer commercial support for it.  So it should "
"not simply be discarded but it is better if the professional support is "
"diversified."
msgstr ""
"Es mejor que haya diferentes empresas ofreciendo servicios comerciales sobre "
"el producto que solo una, ya que en este segundo caso incurriríamos en una "
"mayor dependencia hacia esta empresa. Es habitual un modelo de negocio en el "
"que la misma empresa que desarrolla el producto (quizás sin mucho soporte "
"comunitario externo) ofrezca también soporte comercial sobre este. No se "
"tiene que descartar de entrada, pero es mejor que el soporte profesional se "
"encuentre diversificado."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:251
msgid ""
"The fact that there are already companies offering professional services in "
"relation to a product at the start could also make it easier to carry out a "
"tentative evaluation of the cost of adapting or maintaining it."
msgstr ""
"La existencia de empresas que ya inicialmente ofrecen servicios "
"profesionales sobre un producto puede facilitar también realizar una "
"evaluación tentativa del coste que supondrá adaptarlo o mantenerlo."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:255
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Select components that provide access to development and installation "
"information"
msgstr ""
"Favorecer componentes que faciliten el acceso a la información sobre el "
"desarrollo y la instalación "

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:268
msgid ""
"Transparency is a basic cornerstone of free software.  Without it, it would "
"be very difficult for all the rest to work well."
msgstr ""
"La transparencia es un pilar básico de los proyectos de software libre, sin "
"ella es muy difícil que todo el resto funcione bien."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:270
msgid ""
"If a component has precise, detailed instructions on how to install it, that "
"makes the possibility of carrying out an independent technical assessment of "
"it easier."
msgstr ""
"Que un componente ofrezca instrucciones detalladas y precisas sobre cómo "
"instalarlo facilita que se pueda hacer una evaluación técnica independiente "
"de este."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select components with good code quality metrics"
msgstr "Favorecer componentes con buenas métricas de calidad del código"

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:286
msgid ""
"The fact that project source codes and management tools (bug trackers, mail "
"lists, forums) are public means that it is possible to obtain some objective "
"metrics on free software that it would be very difficult to get in the case "
"of privately owned software."
msgstr ""
"El hecho de que tanto el código como las herramientas de gestión de "
"proyectos (bug-trackers, listas de correo, foros) sean públicas implica que, "
"sobre los proyectos de software libre, sea posible extraer algunas métricas "
"objetivas muy difíciles de conseguir en el caso de software privativo."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:288
msgid "Some metrics that can be obtained for certain projects:"
msgstr ""
"Algunas métricas que se pueden obtener para ciertos proyectos son las "
"siguientes:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:290
msgid "Number of comments, from https://openhub.net/[OpenHub]."
msgstr "Cantidad de comentarios, en https://openhub.net/[OpenHub]."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:292
msgid "Percentage of source code in test cases"
msgstr "Porcentaje de código cubierto por los casos de prueba."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:296
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select components that IMI is already familiar with"
msgstr "Favorecer componentes con los que el IMI ya ha adquirido familiaridad"

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:308
msgid ""
"When we need to adapt an existing source code, if we know the project and "
"the community that sustains it beforehand, it has lots of advantages:"
msgstr ""
"Cuando necesitamos adaptar un componente de software libre ya existente, "
"conocer de antemano el proyecto y la comunidad que lo sustenta presenta "
"muchas ventajas:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:310
msgid "Perhaps IMI has already identified key people in the community."
msgstr ""
"Puede ser que el IMI tenga ya identificadas personas clave dentro de la "
"comunidad."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:312
msgid ""
"It is possible to make a more realistic estimate, in terms of time and "
"money, of the cost of any intended modifications and the possibilities of "
"them being integrated in to the original product."
msgstr ""
"Se puede hacer una estimación más realista del coste en tiempo y en dinero "
"de las modificaciones que se pretende hacer, y de las posibilidades de que "
"sean integradas en el producto original."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:316
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select components that have a licence compatible with the GPL licence"
msgstr "Favorecer componentes con una licencia compatible con la GPL"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:324
msgid ""
"The Free Software Foundation gives this information in its list of licences: "
"https://www.gnu.org/licenses/license-list.en.html."
msgstr ""
"Esta información la ofrece la Free Software Foundation (FSF) en su listado "
"de licencias: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/license-list.es.html."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:327
msgid ""
"The licences in the GPL family are some of the most common.  To avoid "
"licence conflicts with other components we might need, all our components "
"should be GPL-compatible."
msgstr ""
"Las licencias de la familia de la General Public License (GPL) son unas de "
"las más comunes. Para evitar conflictos de licencia con otros componentes "
"que posiblemente necesitaremos, conviene que todos nuestros componentes sean "
"compatibles con GPL."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:331
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select Debian stable components"
msgstr ""
"Favorecer componentes que formen parte de la distribución estable de Debian"

#.   links incoming: link:#M_408[_M_408_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:343
msgid ""
"Any solution component included in Debian’s stable distribution at the "
"project design stage, or which can be run in the stable version without "
"having to be adapted and which is multi-architecture, is considered to be a "
"durable and reliable component."
msgstr ""
"Todo componente de la solución que esté incluido en la distribución estable "
"de Debian en el momento de diseñar el proyecto, o que se pueda ejecutar "
"sobre Debian Estable sin necesidad de adaptación, y que sea "
"multiarquitectura, se considera un componente duradero y fiable."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:345
msgid ""
"Otherwise, select components which, in their standard version downloadable "
"to the project website, can be run on free software platforms, preferably "
"GNU/Linux and without any restrictions in terms of:"
msgstr ""
"Cuando menos, hay que favorecer componentes que puedan ejecutarse, en su "
"versión estándar descargable en la web del proyecto, sobre plataformas "
"libres, preferiblemente GNU/Linux y sin que existan restricciones en cuanto "
"a lo siguiente:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:347
msgid ""
"Requiring a particular GNU/Linux distribution (e.g. a program that only runs "
"in CentOS environments and not on Debian)."
msgstr ""
"Requerir una distribución particular de GNU/Linux (por ejemplo, un software "
"que solo se ejecute en entornos CentOS y no sobre Debian)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:349
msgid ""
"Versions of the main platform elements that are too specific, especially if "
"they are too old or beyond their standard maintenance period (e.g. a program "
"that requires a Linux kernel in a 3.* version, or some basic libraries of "
"the system that are obsolete."
msgstr ""
"Versiones demasiado específicas de los elementos principales de la "
"plataforma, sobre todo si se trata de versiones demasiado antiguas o fuera "
"de su periodo de mantenimiento estándar (por ejemplo, un software que "
"requiera un kernel de Linux en una versión 3.*, o unas librerías básicas del "
"sistema desfasadas)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:351
msgid ""
"Requiring a specific hardware architecture (e.g. solutions that only run on "
"Intel machines)."
msgstr ""
"Requerir una arquitectura de hardware específica (por ejemplo, soluciones "
"que solo se ejecuten en máquinas Intel)."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:355
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Consider all the possibilities and implications before initiating a social "
"fork"
msgstr ""
"Considerar todas las posibilidades y todas las implicaciones antes de "
"iniciar un fork social "

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:363
msgid ""
"When there is a code that has been published with a free licence but the "
"product needs to be developed in a direction that is incompatible with the "
"plans governing the project, it might be necessary to make a fork (in the "
"strict sense of the word, a social fork)."
msgstr ""
"Cuando se dispone de un código que ha sido publicado con licencia libre pero "
"se necesita evolucionar el producto en una dirección incompatible con los "
"planes de quien gobierna el proyecto, puede ser necesario hacer un fork (en "
"el sentido fuerte del término, o social fork)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:367
msgid ""
"Creating a fork has many disadvantages, so it has to be the last resort.  It "
"is much more difficult to share code with the original product once the fork "
"has been created.  And perhaps even more significant, it implies splitting "
"the original community and forcing each developer to decide which version to "
"prioritise."
msgstr ""
"Hacer un fork tiene muchos inconvenientes, y, por lo tanto, tiene que ser el "
"último recurso. Por una parte, dificulta mucho compartir código con el "
"producto original a partir del momento del fork. Y, quizás más "
"significativo, supone dividir la comunidad original y obligar a cada "
"desarrollador a decidir qué proyecto prioriza."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:370
#, no-wrap
msgid "Managing dependencies"
msgstr "Gestión de dependencias"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:377
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Keep a thorough record of all the software packages used, which have to be "
"free software"
msgstr ""
"Llevar un registro exhaustivo de todos los paquetes de software utilizados, "
"que tienen que ser libres "

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:381 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:480 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:507 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:521
msgid "Procurement"
msgstr "Contratar"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:386 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:408 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:424 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:441 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:512 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:526 modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:539
msgid "Publication"
msgstr "Publicación"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:388
msgid ""
"In the case of a contract, include this in the specifications and add that "
"IMI has the last word on including a dependency."
msgstr ""
"En caso de contrato, debe indicarse en los pliegos y añadir que el IMI tiene "
"la última palabra sobre la inclusión de una dependencia."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:390
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procurement Clause: Managing software dependencies"
msgstr "Ejemplo de cláusula: Gestión de las dependencias de software"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:395
msgid ""
"The successful bidder should keep a thorough record of all the software "
"packages used in the solution, which have to be distributed under a software "
"licence accepted by the Free Software Foundation (https://www.gnu.org/"
"licenses/license-list.en.html) or the Open Source Initiative (OSI, https://"
"opensource.org/licenses).  As an additional requirement, the licence for all "
"packages used should not pose any incompatibility problems with the main "
"product licence, EUPL-1.2.  Barcelona City Council reserves the right to "
"demand a software dependency be removed if it considers that it constitutes "
"a legal risk and the successful bidder has to replace the package with "
"another one, or cover the feature with a development of its own."
msgstr ""
"El adjudicatario llevará un registro exhaustivo de todos los paquetes de "
"software utilizados en la solución, que tienen que estar distribuidos bajo "
"una licencia de software aceptada por la Open Source Initiative (OSI, https:/"
"/opensource.org/licenses) o bien por el proyecto GNU (https://www.gnu.org/"
"licenses/license-list.es.html). Como requisito adicional, la licencia de "
"todos los paquetes utilizados no tiene que producir problemas de "
"incompatibilidad con la licencia principal del producto, la EUPL-1.2. El "
"Ayuntamiento de Barcelona se reserva la potestad de exigir que se retire una "
"dependencia de software del producto si considera que puede constituir un "
"riesgo legal y el adjudicatario está obligado a sustituir el paquete por "
"otro, o bien cubrir la funcionalidad con desarrollo propio."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:400
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use a licence monitoring program"
msgstr "Utilizar un software de monitorización de licencias "

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:410
msgid "For example:"
msgstr "Por ejemplo:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:412
msgid "https://www.fossology.org/"
msgstr "https://www.fossology.org/"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:413
msgid "http://creadur.apache.org/"
msgstr "http://creadur.apache.org/"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:418
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Do not copy external dependencies to the repository unless it is an "
"exceptional case"
msgstr ""
"No copiar dependencias externas al repositorio si no es por una causa "
"excepcional"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:428
msgid ""
"Sometimes it is decided to copy a sub-component that is available in an own "
"repository to the repository of the component we are building (whether it is "
"in source, binary or byte code).  The term for this is a bundled dependency. "
" The idea behind it is to make a deployment or development cycle easier, but "
"it is regarded as bad practice because:"
msgstr ""
"A veces se decide copiar un subcomponente que se encuentra disponible en un "
"repositorio propio en el repositorio del componente que estamos construyendo "
"(sea en forma de código fuente, binario o de bytecode). Se dice que esta "
"dependencia se encuentra bundled. A veces se busca con eso un despliegue o "
"un ciclo de desarrollo más sencillo, pero se considera una mala práctica por "
"los siguientes motivos:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:430
msgid ""
"Changes and updates in the sub-component dirty the record of changes to the "
"main component."
msgstr ""
"Los cambios y actualizaciones en el subcomponente ensucian la historia de "
"cambios del componente principal."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:431
msgid ""
"It is more difficult to properly account for the authorship and licensing of "
"each part of the code."
msgstr ""
"Es más difícil dar cuenta correctamente de la autoría y licenciamiento de "
"cada parte del código."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:433
msgid ""
"There might be exceptional circumstances that justify ignoring this measure, "
"but they need to be explained to the project administration."
msgstr ""
"Pueden darse circunstancias excepcionales que justifiquen no obedecer esta "
"medida."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:437
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Look for unsuitable dependencies and find replacements with a free licence"
msgstr ""
"Buscar las dependencias inadecuadas y encontrar sustitutos con licencia "
"libre "

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:444
msgid "The following components need to be deleted:"
msgstr "Deben eliminarse los componentes con las siguientes características:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:446
msgid "Any with a proprietary licence."
msgstr "Con licencia propietaria."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:448
msgid ""
"Any that are owned by Barcelona City Council but cannot be freed for the "
"moment."
msgstr ""
"Propiedad del Ayuntamiento de Barcelona, pero que de momento no se puedan "
"abrir."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:450
msgid ""
"Any that show any kind of licence incompatibility with the other product "
"components to be freed."
msgstr ""
"Que presenten algún tipo de incompatibilidad de licencia con otros "
"componentes del producto que abrir."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:452
msgid "Any that cannot be installed in a free software operating system."
msgstr "Que no puedan ser instalados en un sistema operativo libre."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:456
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finance a security audit of the component to be used"
msgstr "Financiar una auditoría de seguridad del componente que utilizar "

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:466
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finance meetings and hackathons on the component to be used"
msgstr ""
"Financiar encuentros y hackathons relacionadas con el componente que "
"utilizar"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:476
#, no-wrap
msgid "Involve IMI staff in development tasks"
msgstr "Integrar personal del IMI en las tareas de desarrollo"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:486
msgid ""
"This can be done on a contract basis and for any development-related task:"
msgstr ""
"Se puede establecer por contrato y puede ser cualquier tarea relacionada con "
"el desarrollo:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:488
msgid "Writing code"
msgstr "Escritura de código"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:489
msgid "Writing documents"
msgstr "Escritura de documentación"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:490
msgid "Revising code"
msgstr "Revisiones de código"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:491
msgid "Creating, performing and analysing batteries of tests"
msgstr "Creación, ejecución y análisis de baterías de pruebas"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:494
msgid ""
"We want all our staff to be familiar with software that will continue to be "
"used in the future, once the current contract has expired.  The idea being "
"to increase our technological sovereignty and avoid being dependent on "
"single suppliers as much as possible."
msgstr ""
"El objetivo es tener personal propio familiarizado con un software que se "
"seguirá utilizando en el futuro, una vez se acabe el contrato de desarrollo "
"actual. Se trata de profundizar en la soberanía y evitar al máximo la "
"dependencia de proveedores únicos."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:497
#, no-wrap
msgid "Replace the usual private services"
msgstr "Sustitución de servicios privativos habituales"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:503
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use Matomo/Piwik for web analytics"
msgstr "Utilizar Piwik (si se necesita una herramienta de analítica web) "

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:514
msgid "Do not use Google Analytics, use Matomo instead."
msgstr ""
"No hay que utilizar Google Analytics. En su lugar, pueden utilizarse "
"herramientas como Piwik."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:517
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use OpenStreetMap for showing cartographic information"
msgstr ""
"Utilizar OpenStreetMap (si se necesita presentar información cartográfica "
"presente en esta herramienta) "

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:528
msgid ""
"Do not use Google Maps, prefer OSM if cartographic information is required."
msgstr "No hay que utilizar Google Maps."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:531
#, no-wrap
msgid "Publish Android apps in F-Droid"
msgstr ""
"Publicar apps Android en F-Droid (si uno de los productos es una app "
"Android)"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/component-management.adoc:541
msgid ""
"Apps for the Android platform should be published in the free F-Droid "
"repository, as well as Google Play and those most people use."
msgstr ""
"En el caso de apps para la plataforma Android, publicar las apps en el "
"repositorio libre F-Droid, además del repositorio Google Play o aquellos que "
"más personas utilicen."
